{"lemma":"حَظٌّ","slug":"حَظٌّ","root":"ح.ظ.ظ","root_slug":"ح-ظ-ظ","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ظ-ظ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَظّ","root":"حظظ","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8404"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B8%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be fortunate, lucky"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"share, portion, lot (especially of something good)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"luck, good fortune"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"enjoyment, pleasure"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ح ظ ظ (ḥ ẓ ẓ). Compare Ugaritic 𐎈𐎑𐎚 (ḥẓt)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8404","headword_ar":"حَظٌّ","root":"HZ","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good fortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Nh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baxotN","text_ar":"بَخْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Nh:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a share, portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lot:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) or particularly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a share, portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lot, of something good"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K:) some of the people of Hims say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HanozN","text_ar":"حَنْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but when they form a pl., they return to the original, saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuZuwZN","text_ar":"حُظُوظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"is regarded by them as a nasal sound, not as a radical letter: and in like manner they do in the case of every word having a doubled letter, such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruz~N","text_ar":"رُزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^utoruj~N","text_ar":"اُتْرُجٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rNnozN","text_ar":"رٌنْزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^utorunojN","text_ar":"اُتْرُنْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Lth, L:) the pl. (of pauc., S) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHuZ~N","text_ar":"اَحُظٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and (of mult., S)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuZuwZN","text_ar":"حُظُوظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuZuwZapN","text_ar":"حُظُوظَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn- 'Abbád, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiZaAZN","text_ar":"حِظَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IJ, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuZ~N","text_ar":"حُظٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAZK","text_ar":"اَحَاظٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K, [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHaAZN","text_ar":"اَحَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) irregularly, as though it were pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoZK","text_ar":"اَحْظٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,) or it is regularly formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoZK","text_ar":"اَحْظٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter is [irregular, being] originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoZuZN","text_ar":"اَحْظُظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is the original form of the pl. of pauc. mentioned above,] (IB,) and another pl. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiZaA='N","text_ar":"حِظَا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, [and so in the TA as from the K, but in several copies of the K ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiZ~aA='N","text_ar":"حِظَّا=ءٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is of one of the forms of quasi-pl. ns.,]) also irregular, being formed [from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiZaAZN","text_ar":"حِظَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] by a change of the second"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Z","text_ar":"ظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and then into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (L.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaZiyZN","text_ar":"حَظِيظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Nh","Msb","K","Lth","L","AZ","IJ","IB"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}